// Semantic direction:
// graphql provides a type-safe query language where clients specify exactly what data they need.
// skjema_bygg assembles type_definisjon entries into an executable schema.
// resolver_fn maps each felt in the schema to a function that fetches its value.
// resolver_kontekst carries per-request data (authenticated user, database connection, etc).
// dataylaster batches N resolver calls into one laster_batch fetch, solving the N+1 problem.
// laster_schedule defers execution until all resolvers in the current tick have registered keys.
// n_pluss_én_gql is the anti-pattern where loading N parent objects triggers N child queries.
// introspeksjon lets clients query the schema itself; introspeksjon_deaktiver hides it in production.
// persisted_queries stores approved query hashes server-side, rejecting arbitrary client queries.
// query_kompleksitet assigns a cost to each felt; kompleksitet_grense prevents expensive queries.
// dybde_grense prevents deeply nested queries that traverse many relation levels.
// kjøre_kontekst_autorisasjon_gql checks permissions per resolver before returning data.
// feltautentisering applies direktiv-based rules (e.g. @requiresRole) to individual felter.
// delvis_resultat returns successfully resolved fields alongside feil_liste_gql for failed ones.
// abonnement_gql pushes real-time updates to clients via WebSocket (ws_protokoll_gql) or SSE.
// abonnement_publiser sends a new value to all filtered abonnement subscribers.
// cache_policy_cache_first returns cached data immediately, refreshing in the background.
// optimistisk_respons updates the local cache before the server confirms, reducing perceived latency.
// kodegenerering_gql produces typed Norscode structs and query hooks from a schema file.

// Primitive flow:
// spørring: klient sender { bruker(id: "1") { navn, email } }
//   server: parse -> valider mot skjema -> sjekk kompleksitet/dybde
//   kjøre: resolver(bruker, {id:"1"}, kontekst) -> DB.finn(1)
//   felt navn: standard_resolver(bruker.navn) | tilpasset: resolver_fn
//   returner JSON-resultat
// N+1 løsning: innlegg[].forfatter -> dataylaster.last(forfatter_id)
//   schedule: samle alle forfatter_ider -> batch_funksjon([id1,id2,...]) -> én DB-spørring
// abonnement: klient abonnerer på meldingMottat(kanal: "123")
//   server: pub_sub_gql.abonner(kanal) -> ny melding publisert
//   -> abonnement_filter(melding) -> send over ws til klient
// klient cache: spørring_send -> cache_policy_cache_first
//   cache treff: returner straks -> bakgrunnsoppdatering
//   cache bom: nettverk_first -> lagre i klient_cache_gql

// This defines a GraphQL server and client: schema definition, resolvers, DataLoader batching,
// complexity limits, subscriptions, client-side caching, and code generation.
